<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1997) - SECTION 3.5: CIRCUIT FUNCTION AND DIAGNOSTICS - ENGINE OIL
        PRESSURE (EOP) SENSOR - FAULT DETECTION/MANAGEMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FAULT DETECTION/MANAGEMENT</title>
        <para>An EOP signal that is detected out of range high or low by the ECM will cause the engine to ignore the EOP
            signal and disable Engine Warning and Protection.
        </para>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The EOP sensor only reads 0-38 psi.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef1251889">3.96</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            and
            <emph type="bold">Table
                <hotlnk xrefid="et1251814">3.19</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the circuit diagram and table for the Engine Oil Pressure Sensor (EOP).
        </para>
        <figure id="ef1251889" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg1127" filename="../figeg1/EG1127.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3.96 - Engine Oil Sensor Circuit Diagram</caption>
        </figure>
